    "It is also relevant to note that model classification in our approach performs more effectively when the cut-off score is set at 18, achieving a weighted F1 score of 0.89, in contrast to 0.84 achieved with the cut-off score of 25 applied that was found to be ideal within a German population sample.",
    "This was discovered during the analysis of the ROC curve distribution scores.",
